  "courseAscendingIntervalsTitle": "Master ascending intervals",
  "courseAscendingIntervalsGoal": "Hear the distance when the melody goes upward.",
  "courseAscendingIntervalsCard1Title": "Concept",
  "courseAscendingIntervalsCard1Body": "The first note is the root. The second note tells you the interval size upward.",
  "courseAscendingIntervalsCard2Title": "Ear clue",
  "courseAscendingIntervalsCard2Body": "Sing the first note in your head, then feel how far the second note climbs.",
  "courseAscendingIntervalsCard3Title": "Mini drill",
  "courseAscendingIntervalsCard3Body": "Start with unison, octave, fifth, and thirds before adding seconds and sevenths.",
  "courseDescendingIntervalsTitle": "Master descending intervals",
  "courseDescendingIntervalsGoal": "Recognize the same distance when the melody falls.",
  "courseDescendingIntervalsCard1Title": "Concept",
  "courseDescendingIntervalsCard1Body": "The first note is high, then the sound falls to the root. The interval name is still the distance.",
  "courseDescendingIntervalsCard2Title": "Ear clue",
  "courseDescendingIntervalsCard2Body": "Do not answer “lower” automatically. Keep the first note in memory and measure the fall.",
  "courseDescendingIntervalsCard3Title": "Mini drill",
  "courseDescendingIntervalsCard3Body": "Practice the same interval ascending then descending until the distance feels identical.",
  "courseHarmonicIntervalsTitle": "Hear two notes together",
  "courseHarmonicIntervalsGoal": "Identify intervals when both notes sound at the same time.",
  "courseHarmonicIntervalsCard1Title": "Concept",
  "courseHarmonicIntervalsCard1Body": "Both notes arrive together, so you hear color more than melody.",
  "courseHarmonicIntervalsCard2Title": "Ear clue",
  "courseHarmonicIntervalsCard2Body": "Listen for stability and tension: calm, open, bright, dark, rubbing, unresolved.",
  "courseHarmonicIntervalsCard3Title": "Mini drill",
  "courseHarmonicIntervalsCard3Body": "After a wrong answer, replay the correct interval and name its color before moving on.",
  "courseMixedIntervalsTitle": "Mixed interval survival",
  "courseMixedIntervalsGoal": "Answer by distance, even when the direction changes every question.",
  "courseMixedIntervalsCard1Title": "Concept",
  "courseMixedIntervalsCard1Body": "Mixed mode removes the training wheels. Every question can change direction.",
  "courseMixedIntervalsCard2Title": "Ear clue",
  "courseMixedIntervalsCard2Body": "First identify direction, then distance. Do not let direction steal the answer.",
  "courseMixedIntervalsCard3Title": "Mini drill",
  "courseMixedIntervalsCard3Body": "Use easier intervals first, then unlock the full set when accuracy is stable.",
  "courseMistakeReviewTitle": "Turn mistakes into training",
  "courseMistakeReviewGoal": "Use the summary screen to attack your real weak spots.",
  "courseMistakeReviewCard1Title": "Concept",
  "courseMistakeReviewCard1Body": "A wrong answer is a clue. The confusion tells you which two sounds your ear merges.",
  "courseMistakeReviewCard2Title": "Ear clue",
  "courseMistakeReviewCard2Body": "Use “Review my mistakes” while the sound is still fresh in memory.",
  "courseMistakeReviewCard3Title": "Mini drill",
  "courseMistakeReviewCard3Body": "Train only the missed intervals for one short session, then return to mixed practice."
